It gets little busy on Sundays but I came in here today and it was swift.. ordered lots of bobas.. chocolate good watermelon taro smoothie my favorite So clean inside the AC works and friendly staff A+ clean bathroom!!! Ss

A friend and I visited this place a while back excited to support a store in our neighborhood. Sad to say that my expectations was the worst. I order a protein smoothie from their menu, and while the smoothie was indeed great tasting. The hospitality from the owners and employee left a bad taste in my mouth. After I order my smoothie I ask for my receipt, like anyone would and I noticed that they charge me a higher price than what was listed on their menu. When I asked why, the women who was on cashier proceeded to inform me that they didn't yet update their pos system with the correct price. I'm pissed at this point because they knowingly charge me a higher price and hoped that I wouldn't ask for my receipt. Before I can get another word out, one of the employees from the back, who made the smoothie came around towards the front and open the cashier machine and shoved a dollar in my face as if that would solve the problem. I highly dissapointed with the way I was treated by supporting a local shop near me. Never again will I give my hard earned money to this shop again.

Amazing smoothies, juices, wraps, bowls, sandwiches, sambusas and soups. I have come here a lot and I like this place a lot! Affordable prices and very good and healthy food. Almost everything is vegan there. Very friendly owners and staff and there is always a very good atmosphere.
we were welcomed with open arms in the middle of a winter storm set back in March 2018 juices, appetizers, a list many things, we ordered food and drinks to go... it was healthy and delicious....
The gift is my favorite!
LOVE this place! A hidden Harlem gem. Lovely staff and amazing smoothies at reasonable prices - I highly recommend The Gift!

Good food and juice made with fresh ingredients. Get the tuna sandwich with delicious green sauce. All of the juices and smoothies are great. Eat healthy here and support local business. There’s no catch!

Highly recommend standing behind this juice bar and initiative with Oasis Powerhouse! Try the quinoa veggie bowl 10/10 as far as nourishing and the Time Square

Reasonable prices, and I learned last year they deliver! Not that I mind the walk or short wait. Breakfast egg white pancake platter is quite the treat.

I order  salads and juices once a week and they are always fresh ! Great option for a lightermeal. It's also a super close walk from downtown as well as an option on Ny ! Love their can't toxic juice.

The drinks and food are amazing. I've been a customer for the past 3 years. The Blake King smoothie is no joke, contains caffeine. It should not be messed with at night; its a natural red bull. If you have any ailments or just some need sustenance their drinks can get you back on track. Their oatmeal is also a boss and I also enjoy their other offerings on the menu!!!

Best smoothie of my life! Unreal. So fresh. So refreshing. Can't wait to return even though I'm not in that area often. Prices so fair. I loved that i could create my own. I got mine with figs, hemp milk, and avocado and a few other things. Mindblown. Best. Ever. And staff so nice. Place is so chill & positive, too. And it's right by bus stop and train station. Sweet!
Fresh, quick, delicious juices! The “Hangover” is my favorite!
Love the juices and smoothies here. I also love all the other healthy food options like the bowls and the oatmeal. Great place.

I love the fact that you can create your own blends here and the prices are very low. They have a wide selection of options.  The only thing that I don't like is that both their almond and soy milks are sweetened - not a good option if you want to avoid added sugars.
You will not regret coming to Oasis Jimma Juice. My apartment is just around the corner and I frequent this place for affordable, healthful and sustainable smoothies. It'd be a mistake not to try it.
Service is beyond exceptional and smoothies/breakfast menus are also really good.
Food is tasty, afforable, and healthy! A lot of variety. The owner is a traveler and a very genuine, kind person. Highly recommend the acai bowls!
You're doing absolutely fantastic job. Proud of you

The BEST of the BEST!!!  The food is "out of this world"; very tasty, very colorful and very affordable. The smoothies/juices are something that you don't want to end..Very refreshing, delicious and very enjoyable to look at. I told all my friends about this wonderful experience and I am eager to return. All the best to the team and the wonderful owner; extremely friendly and very pleasant to talk to. Liana & Radu

AND CREATE YOUR OWN   CONCOCTIONS : WITH CHOICES LIE FRESH PAPAYA, PASSION FRUIT, PINEAPPLE,  you can even add pistachio butter or almond or other butters... macca, been pollen or other super foods... acai...etc! and have amazing fresh organic home made soups, wraps, quinoa bowls and MUCH MORE!! AMAZING!! And the friendliest people on EARTH who absolutely LOVE their customers!!

Excellent customer service and great choices got healthy eating. Tasty!
Huge volume of salad! a few good vegan options, good for student :)

This place has such great vibes. I came here with a friend during happy hour and I was very pleased. We were seated and tended to immediately. Our servers were pleasant and our food came at just the right time. All the while, there's laughter all around. The space is on the smaller side, but small in a cozy kind of way that really lends itself to a positive atmosphere.  As far as food goes, I ordered the Chimi burger with taro chips which was delicious, definitely one of the better burgers I've had in NYC. The happy hour tequila sunrise was very good for only $5; it looked small but it was strong and more than fair for the price. I would definitely recommend Solace as a place to kick back and enjoy some good food & drinks with friends.

The Oasis Juice Bar is so delicious and reviving - We came from Buffalo for vacation purpose and were looking for some juice bar in the middle of the day, which really can cool us off  from the hot New York City weather and the crowd. After a little research online, we finally found  Oasis Juice Bar at the corner of 3163 Broadway, New York. We were glad we run into this Juice Bar. It's an extraordinary lift me-up in the wake of a prolonged day. I've attempted things from the breakfast and lunch menus, and they've been yummy without fail. Their Customer Service is great as well! In addition to their incredible juices and Salad, their costs are exceptionally affordable. I would highly recommend this Juice Bar to any visitors  in New York City to spare a little of your  busy time and pay visit to this area, I guarantee,  you won’t be disappointed because I was not.
Clean place and friendly staff and amazing salad and Juice . They treat customer like a family . Thank you Oasis Juice Bar. I will come back soon for sure.

This is such a great addition to this area. I've been looking for a place to satisfy my juice craving and i finally found it. You walk in and the place smells so good. The quality of the fruit available is exceptional (I'd say on a Whole Food level). The people that work are nice, calm and friendly. Not the place to go if you're in a rush. They even give you the extra juice and are fine if you want to customize your drink.  Can't wait to go back.
